  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Pseudo-hermitian and <math altimg="si11.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="script">P</mi><mi>T</mi></math> -symmetric quantum systems with energy-dependent potentials: Bound-state solutions and energy spectra</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-09</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We introduce generalized versions of complex Scarf and Morse-type potentials that contain energy-dependent parameters. <math altimg="si11.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="script">P</mi><mi>T</mi></math> -symmetry and pseudo-hermiticity of the associated quantum systems are discussed, and a modified orthogonality relation and pseudo-norm are constructed. We show that despite energy-dependence, our systems can admit real energy spectra and normalizable solutions of bound-state type.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
